answers.body_markdown:
I would use a [`BitSet`][1].

Advantage: Fast scan for missing value. Performance: _O(n)_

```lang-java
public static int solution(int... values) {
	BitSet bitSet = new BitSet();
	for (int v : values)
		if (v &gt; 0)
			bitSet.set(v);
	return bitSet.nextClearBit(1);
}
```

*Test*

```lang-java
System.out.println(solution(1, 3, 6, 4, 1, 2));
System.out.println(solution(1, 2, 3));
System.out.println(solution(-1, -3));
```

*Output*

```lang-none
5
4
1
```


  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/BitSet.html

